We came across an interesting problem today with some code which was unexpectedly returning nil.
The code that we had looked like this&hellip;
class SomeClass def our_method	a_hash = { :a =&gt; 2 } a_hash.merge!({:b =&gt; 3}) unless some_condition.nil? end end  &hellip;and we didn&rsquo;t notice the &lsquo;unless&rsquo; statement on the end which meant that if &lsquo;some_condition&rsquo; was nil then the return value of the method would be nil.
One way around it is to ensure that we explicitly return a_hash at the end of the method&hellip;

